{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784171750,"nonce":"OKABt8esDZB0/f9TYyQs/iSIvHM=","message":"CLOSED — MERGED PR #108 (squash `cd9fdef`).\n\nResolved with the \"preserve on MySQL + reject the impossible\" approach.\n\n**Split general-cast rendering from result-pin rendering** via a new `Dialect::write_general_cast_type` (called at the one general-cast site in `view_render.rs`; result pins keep `write_cast_type`). The runtime query path has no general-cast arm, so scope is confined to check/generated/index/view-body expressions.\n\n**MySQL now renders `DECIMAL(p, s)` faithfully** and the reverse-parser `general_cast` guard relaxes so MySQL decimal casts structure and round-trip; `canonical_mysql_cast_type` preserves scale (a genuine scale change still diffs). Explicit `DECIMAL(65, 0)` stays a real decimal (not the `I128` pin representative).\n\n**Reject the impossible, loud at render** (not silent narrowing): a `Decimal` cast on SQLite, a 128-bit-int general cast on every backend (shared `reject_128bit_general_cast`), and a MySQL decimal outside `1 \u003c= precision \u003c= 65` / `scale \u003c= 30` / `scale \u003c= precision`. PostgreSQL unchanged (`numeric(p, s)` already faithful).\n\n**Consistency across render paths** — the incremental plan path canonicalizes before rendering, so the canonicalizers must not flip a cast's render decision: SQLite keeps a 128-bit cast un-folded (so the reject fires on the plan path too, not only direct render); PostgreSQL preserves render-OK bare-`numeric` targets (`U64`, `Raw(\"numeric\")`/`Raw(\"decimal\")`) the pin fold would otherwise collapse to a rejected `I128`. Decimal precision/scale conversions are checked, so an authored `DECIMAL(4294967306, 2)` stays `Raw` rather than wrapping.\n\n**Local codex:** clean after the initial pass + six edge-hardening rounds (SQLite plan-path bypass; MySQL `DECIMAL(65,0)` round-trip; MySQL DECIMAL range; zero precision; PG `U64` direct-vs-plan consistency; PG `Raw` numeric targets; checked `u32` decimal conversion). Full `--all-features` workspace tests, clippy, and the live MySQL / PostgreSQL `#[ignore]` suites pass on fresh DBs, including a new live MySQL test that a decimal-cast check re-plans empty and that a scale change diffs.\n\n**Out of scope (noted):** MySQL's `DECIMAL(65,0)` ↔ `I128` pin spelling collision is inherent to the pin vocabulary (general casts sidestep it); the pre-existing PG `U64`/bare-numeric general-cast re-plan churn is orthogonal — this change only makes its render paths consistent, without newly rejecting it (flagged to the maintainer, who accepted).","files":null}]}